Fig. S2. Inﬂuence of the endogenous circadian system on cardiovascular function at rest. Cosine models of variables at rest revealed a signiﬁcant fundamental circadian rhythm for epinephrine, norepinephrine, cortisol, HF, pNN50, SBP, DBP, and HR, and a harmonic rhythm (i.e., with a period of ≈12 h) for platelet aggregability. Platelet count did not show signiﬁcant rhythmicity. Note, so that higher putative risk is upwards for all variables, the y axes for the vagal markers HF and pNN50 (Bottom Left) are inverted, i.e., upwards corresponds to vagal withdrawal. This is different from the orientation of these variables in Fig. 2 of the main manuscript. Symbols as in Fig. S1. *Timing of the peak for signiﬁcant fundamental circadian cycle; #timing of the peaks for signiﬁcant second harmonic of circadian cycle.

